bug.short_desc: A package is removed yet gnome software considers the package to be still installed.
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1176160 What really happens with an uninstalled package.
Description of problem: I uninstalled a package with gnome software. It got uninstalled but when I search for the package again in gnome - software it appears installed. I remove it and this message comes up.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): 3.20.3
How reproducible: Always
Steps to Reproduce: 1.Install something from gnome software 2.Uninstall it using gnome software 3.Search for the same package in gnome software and it appears installed. Try to remove it.
Actual results: There is an error message saying the package is not installed yet it appears installed.
Expected results: The package should appear uninstalled and be ready to be re-installed if needed.
Additional info: The problem goes away after a restart.

attachment.desc: What really happens with an uninstalled package.
